description:
&lt;p&gt;Locum Consultant Obstetrician and Gynaecologist with a special interest in Urogynaecology&lt;br /&gt;Princess Alexandra Hospital NHS Trust&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Applications are invited for a fixed term, full time locum Consultant Obstetrician &amp; Gynaecologist with a special interest in Urogynaecology, to join an existing team of 11 Consultant Obstetricians &amp; Gynaecologists, 1 Consultant Gynaecologists, 1 Obstetrician, 2 Associate specialists at the Princess Alexandra Hospital NHS Trust, Harlow. The post is a combined post with alternate week theatre session and alternate week gynaecology clinic in addition to participation in gynaecological emergency cover in and out of hours. The post holder will be expected to participate in the day to day running of the women’s health unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will participate in the Obstetric hot week consultant rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be a 1:14 on call with prospective cover.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post attracts 10 PAs (8.5 DCC, 1.5 SPAs)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Department of Obstetrics and Gynaecology consists of an integral maternity and gynaecology unit on a single site, based at the Princess Alexandra Hospital. Inpatients are based at the Princess Alexandra Hospital, while clinics are held at Princess Alexandra Hospital, St Margaret’s Hospital (Epping) and Herts &amp; Essex Hospital, (Bishop’s Stortford).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Essential criteria:&lt;br /&gt;Full GMC registration&lt;br /&gt;• Relevant CCT or equivalent (to be confirmed by PMETB/GMC by date of AAC)&lt;br /&gt;• Entry onto the GMC Specialist Register or eligibility for entry within 6 months of the date of the AAC&lt;br /&gt;• MRCOG&lt;br /&gt;• ATSM in advanced labour ward practice&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clinical training and experience in general Obstetrics and Gynaecology equivalent to that required for a UK CCT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mr Ling Wee CSG Lead consultant in Obs and Gynae&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address Ling.wee@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mr Wee - Clinical Service Group lead may be contacted for an informal visit via our Divisional PA Anna-Marie Hayes on 01279 444455 ext. 7104&lt;/p&gt;
